name: Frequency Modulators
description: Can be used to upgrade the components of the USS Franklin. Frequency Modulators regulate signals coming in and out of Swarm units. Perhaps this knowledge can be used against them...

name: Franklin Warp Interlock
description: Can be used to upgrade the Warp Engine component of the USS Franklin. The Warp Interlock upgrade can be fitted onto a vessel's warp core to prevent overheating during long journeys.

name: Franklin Warp Conduit
description: Can be used to upgrade the Warp Engine component of the USS Franklin. The Warp Conduit makes travel by warp possible by transferring power from the Warp Core to the Warp Engines. Newer conduits allow for a greater power transfer without endangering the Warp Core.

name: Franklin Warp Relay
description: Can be used to upgrade the Warp Engine component of the USS Franklin. Warp Relays are the primary component of Warp Engines aboard the vast majority of Starships. They allow for the conversion of ionized Dilithium into energy.

name: Franklin Warp Regulator
description: Can be used to upgrade the Warp Engine component of the USS Franklin. A Warp Regulator is a relatively recent invention, created after a series of accidents involving NX class starships. It regulates the power flow from the Warp Core to the Engines.

name: Franklin Warp Injector
description: Can be used to upgrade the Warp Engine component of the USS Franklin. A Warp Injector allows for ionized Dilithium to be inserted directly into the Warp Core, increasing power output by a wide margin. This should only ever be used in conjunction with proper Warp regulation.

name: Franklin Warp Containment
description: Can be used to upgrade the Warp Engine component of the USS Franklin. The Warp Containment unit helps to contain energy leakage throughout the power transfer process. This reduces energy waste and allows for higher speeds during warp travel.

name: Franklin Warp Coil
description: Can be used to upgrade the Warp Engine component of the USS Franklin. Mounted within the warp nacelles, the primary and secondary warp coils use the plasma generated by the warp core to create a subspace displacement field that allows for faster-than-light travel.

name: Franklin Warp Core
description: Can be used to upgrade the Warp Engine component of the USS Franklin. Warp Core is the common designation for the main energy reactor powering the propulsion system on warp-capable starships. More modern Warp Cores allow for greater speeds while not endangering the Warp Engines.
